# ShopTheBarber â€” Root env example
# Backend env vars live in server/.env (see server/.env.example).
# Copy server/.env.example to server/.env and configure JWT_SECRET, Stripe, Resend, etc.
#
# Frontend (Vite): create .env or .env.local in project root for local dev.
# In production (Vercel), set these in the dashboard.
# - VITE_API_URL          (required in prod) Backend URL, e.g. https://shopthebarber-api.onrender.com
# - VITE_sovereign_APP_ID  (optional) Legacy app param
# - VITE_sovereign_BACKEND_URL (optional) Legacy backend URL
#
# Analytics (optional; set one of GA, PostHog, Plausible, Mixpanel)
# - VITE_GA_MEASUREMENT_ID   Google Analytics 4 (e.g. G-XXXXXXXXXX)
# - VITE_POSTHOG_KEY         PostHog project API key (analytics + nav tracking)
# - VITE_POSTHOG_HOST        e.g. https://app.posthog.com
# - VITE_PLAUSIBLE_DOMAIN    e.g. yourapp.com
# - VITE_MIXPANEL_TOKEN      Mixpanel project token
#
# Security / Error tracking (optional)
# - VITE_SENTRY_DSN          Sentry DSN for frontend errors
#
# Full list: docs/WORLD_CLASS_ROADMAP_AND_ENV.md
